OL,4,CMay Day Morris dancers wear blue makeup
OL,5,Cover racism fears
OL,6, A group of Morris dancers have changed
OL,7, their face paint from black to blue
OL,8, following concerns over racism.
OL,10,FMembers of the Hook Eagle Morris Men
OL,11,Fshowcased their new look at a
OL,12,Fperformance near Hook, Hampshire, to
OL,13,Fmark the May Day dawn earlier.
OL,15,FIt follows concerns about using
OL,16,Fblack-face raised by the Black Lives
OL,17,FMatter movement last year.
OL,19,FDancer John Ellis, 70, said it was "by
OL,20,Ffar and away the biggest change" in the
OL,21,Fgroup's 30-year history.
